The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Rap after child slap

 Krishnagar, Sept. 5: A Nadia court today asked parents of schoolchildren to be sensitive towards their needs while hearing the plight of three girls who had had fled home after being thrashed for chatting with boys. 

 Piyali Debnath, Madhuri Saha and Sephali Rajbangshi, all Class IX students of Nabadwip Jatiya Girls School and daughters of well-to-do businessmen, left home together yesterday. They were found waiting for a bus on National Highway 34 in Krishnagar about 15 km from their home in Nabadwip this morning.

 The assistant chief judicial magistrate of Nabadwip court, Shiv Shankar Ghosh, criticised the girls parents for becoming insensitive. 

 Ghosh stressed the need for parents to be tolerant while dealing with children.




